CNCP v1 23557
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#7980: <style scoped> doesn't work on SFC components created by render functions",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:24:44.634518+00:00",
  "text": "<style scoped> doesn't work on SFC components created by render functions\n\n### Vue version\r\n\r\n3.2.47\r\n\r\n### Link to minimal reproduction\r\n\r\nhttps://codesandbox.io/p/sandbox/prod-sun-sjr86q?file=%2Fsrc%2FApp.vue\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Use these packages: \r\n```\r\n\"vue\": \"^3.2.47\",   \r\n\"vite\": \"^4.2.1\",\r\n\"@vitejs/plugin-vue-jsx\": \"^3.0.1\",\r\n```\r\n\r\n2. Create a JSX component (or a component created with `h()`) in a SFC `<script setup>` and add it to a `<template>`. Use a `<style scoped>` in the same file where the JSX component is defined.\r\n\r\n\r\n### What is expected?\r\n\r\n- <style scoped> works on SFC JSX. More specifically, `data-v-<hash>` added to the child elements of the JSX\r\n\r\n### What is actually happening?\r\n\r\n4. The scoped style doesn't apply to the SFC, because the `data-v-<hash>` attributes are only added to the outmost html element of the JSX.\r\n\r\n5. If I use a `computed` wrapping a JSX, the scoped style works properly. However, I don't want to use computed to a JSX because there are props I want to pass to a JSX, and `computed` can't take any parameter.\r\n\r\n4.1. If I use a `h()`, the `data-v-<hash>` attribute isn't even added to the component.\r\n\r\nIn both cases, I can work through this by using CSS modules. But it would be better if I could use the scoped style because I don't need to inject a class var to each element.\r\n\r\n\r\n### System Info\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Any additional comments?\r\n\r\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    ":sparkles: feature request",
    "scope: sfc"
  ],
